OL,3,CCoroner rules medical expert 'not
OL,4,Cbiased' against Ian Paterson
OL,6,FHe has however has decided that the
OL,7,Fexpert will not be part of the team
OL,8,Fcurrently reviewing some further cases
OL,9,Fand his evidence will only be called
OL,10,Fupon when the Coroner asks for it, or
OL,11,Fif parties request it. This is
OL,12,Fsomething he says is not "a criticism
OL,13,Fof his (Profession Dixon's)
OL,14,Fprofessional integrity."
OL,16,FThe Coroner has also decided that
OL,17,Fthere needs to be a timetable, sooner
OL,18,Frather than later, to discuss the
OL,19,Fdebate there is surrounding "generic
OL,20,Fcausation issues."
