OL,6,F(b) The local recurrence causes or
OL,7,Fmore than minimally, trivially or
OL,8,Fnegligibly contributes to the deceased
OL,9,Fdeveloping metastatic disease;
OL,11,F(c) The deceased dies of metastatic
OL,12,Fdisease.
OL,14,FHowever experts on behalf of Spire
OL,15,FHealthcare point to reports that
OL,16,Fsuggest that a mastectomy leaving
OL,17,Fbehind breast tissue such as the
OL,18,F"cleavage sparing mastectomy"
OL,19,Fpracticed by Mr Paterson gives no
OL,20,Fgreater risk to recurrence or
OL,21,Fmortality.
